{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"739adfcb-1dbd-4035-b6cd-eb65b7456af4","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod, Ignore(\"Blocked by #1234\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by #1234\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test, Ignore(\"Blocked by #1234\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test, Skip(\"Blocked by #1234\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nNote: xUnit is the only one where the skip reason is a **named parameter** on the test attribute itself rather than a separate attribute.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0c5aa41a-fed0-471a-9b9a-6298b2943207","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":300,"requestId":"7C1C:1986A2:12777D4:14EA80D:69F943A3"},"id":"43f242e7-57d0-47b6-8ec6-bdbb2ed84b67","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:11:05.685Z","parentId":"cef27c26-082b-4c2c-b43a-4d3fcfe25056"}
